Please, does anyone have a JSPParser class that parses JSPs?

I hacked the HTMLParser class that comes in the Lucene demo and made it =
parse and index JSPs. But when i would do a search, the jsp tags=20

 <%pageContext.setAttribute( "req", request );%>=20
<%@ page import=3D"com.propelnewmedia.tags.BreadcrumbTrailer"%>


and so on, were included in the summary.=20
Then, I figured out a way to get the JSP tags out of the summary (and i =
think out of the index as well).=20

What I did was designate JSP tags (anything starting with <% and ending =
with %>) as a 3rd comment type in the void CommentTag() :, TOKEN :, and =
<WithinCommentN> TOKEN : sections of HTMLParser.jj=20

I just copied and pasted the relevant code for Comment2 and mimicked =
that for my new Comment type. I then recompiled HTMLParser.jj using =
javacc.=20

I'm still not out of the woods though. I still need to know how to make =
Lucene not include list element values, etc in the search hits. For =
instance, if a keyword happens to be in a <selection> list, it gets =
counted as a hit.=20

Any suggestions (or preferably, working code) would be massively =
appreciated!. Thanks in advance.


